\begin_inset Formula $X\to X$
\end_inset

 defined by 
\begin_inset Formula $x\mapsto x.g$
\end_inset

 is continuous (and hence a homeomorphism, as the action of 
\begin_inset Formula $g^{-1}$
\end_inset

