\begin_inset Formula $U\subset X$
\end_inset

 is open if and only if 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap U_{h}$
\end_inset

 is open in 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{h}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap U_{v}$
\end_inset

 is open in 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{v}$
\end_inset

.
 Let's calculate the transition maps 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{vh}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{hv}$
\end_inset

.
 We have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\varphi_{vh}(c,d) & =\varphi_{v}\circ\varphi_{h}^{-1}(c,d)\\
 & =\varphi_{v}\left(\ell_{c,d}^{h}\right)\\
 & =\varphi_{v}\left(\ell_{\frac{1}{c},-\frac{d}{c}}^{v}\right)\\
 & =\left(\frac{1}{c},-\frac{d}{c}\right),
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which is 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{\infty}$
\end_inset

 whenever 
\begin_inset Formula $c\neq0$
\end_inset

.
 Similarly, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\varphi_{hv}(a,b) & =\varphi_{h}\circ\varphi_{v}^{-1}(a,b)\\
 & =\varphi_{h}\left(\ell_{a,b}^{v}\right)\\
 & =\varphi_{h}\left(\ell_{\frac{1}{a},-\frac{b}{a}}^{h}\right)\\
 & =\left(\frac{1}{a},-\frac{b}{a}\right),
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which is 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{\infty}$
\end_inset

 whenever 
\begin_inset Formula $a\neq0$
\end_inset

.
 Altogether, our gluing data consists of
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Omega_{1}=\Omega_{2}=\mathbb{R}^{2},\qquad\Omega_{12}=\Omega_{21}=\{(a,b)\in\mathbb{R}^{2}\mid a\neq0\},\qquad\phi_{12}:(a,b)\mapsto\left(\frac{1}{a},-\frac{b}{a}\right).
\]

